law.text:
The court disposition level of the system shall consist of at least the following information as relates to the offenses charged and the offenses disposed of:
The court which disposed of the offense;
The name of the presiding judge;
Date upon which the trial began;
The final pleading, as to each charged offense and the level thereof;
Listing of charged offenses disposed of by the court together with:
Date of disposition;
Listing of each offense and the KRS number, name and level;
Whether the offense was dismissed in exchange for a guilty plea on another offense; and
Number of offenses disposed of by the court;
Listing of offenses for which the defendant was convicted by KRS number, name and level;
Number of convicted offenses; and
Date of conviction.
